ctive on Consumer Rights. The Acquis Principles include:- General rules formulated on the basis of existing EC law- An accompanying commentary, outlining the foundations in the Acquis- Definitions of core legal terms and a glossary on terminology The Acquis Group aims to reformulate the present patchwork of directives, regulations and judgments on EC private law as a coherent Restatement, the Acquis Principles (ACQP). These Principles present the current state of EC law in a structure which allows readers to identify commonalities, contradictions and gaps in the Acquis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBreach of contractzEuropean Union countries. 0aContractszEuropean Union countries. 0aPerformance (Law)zEuropean Union countries. 0aRemedies (Law)zEuropean Union countries. 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist History 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062100608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2009z9783899496871oZDB-23-DGC40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978386653873340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783866538733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783866538733/original  a978-3-11-021952-4  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009b2009  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062100-6  DGBA